    {
      "id": "ZDAxRcqG-PD8nIfCQ25d5",
      "type": "text",
      "x": -6141.288640516277,
      "y": -13257.212831415081,
      "width": 1041.9189453125,
      "height": 240,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#343a40",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 4,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "bm9",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 2146141198,
      "version": 1885,
      "versionNonce": 766922892,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1774965793777,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Question: Are Build Tools and Bundlers one and the same? \nBundler reads the source code, builds a dependency graph and produces an output (single file or a bundle).\nIt seems that most bundlers are effectively build tools, because they rarely just bundle the code (e.g. Webpack's loaders and plugins)\n\n\nWebpack - a bunlder with loaders and plugins. Complicated setup, does too many things.\n\nVite - calls itself a build tool, uses a separate bundler and compiler. \nVite simplifies/abstracts the manual setup done in Webpack, via sensible defaults and templates.\n\nNx - a technology agnostic build platform (or a build system) with a task runner. \nIt orchestrate tasks across multiple projects and executes different build tools (Vite, Webpack, Cradle, Maven, etc.)",
      "fontSize": 16,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Question: Are Build Tools and Bundlers one and the same? \nBundler reads the source code, builds a dependency graph and produces an output (single file or a bundle).\nIt seems that most bundlers are effectively build tools, because they rarely just bundle the code (e.g. Webpack's loaders and plugins)\n\n\nWebpack - a bunlder with loaders and plugins. Complicated setup, does too many things.\n\nVite - calls itself a build tool, uses a separate bundler and compiler. \nVite simplifies/abstracts the manual setup done in Webpack, via sensible defaults and templates.\n\nNx - a technology agnostic build platform (or a build system) with a task runner. \nIt orchestrate tasks across multiple projects and executes different build tools (Vite, Webpack, Cradle, Maven, etc.)",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
